properties.areaDesc: Los Angeles County Coast including Downtown Los Angeles
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued March 3 at 3:29AM PST until March 3 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...North to northeast winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 35
mph expected.

* WHERE...Below passes and canyons from Malibu to the Hollywood
Hills in the Los Angeles County Coast.

* WHEN...Until noon PST today.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Major roadways that could be impacted by
the gusty winds include the Pacific Coast Highway, and the 10
and 405 freeways.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON PST TODAY
